Watershed segmentation¶

In [17]:
def segment_watershed(image):
    gray = cv2.cvtColor(image,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    
    image_byte = img_as_ubyte(gray)

    denoised = rank.median(image_byte, disk(2))

    markers = rank.gradient(denoised, disk(5)) < 10
    markers = ndi.label(markers)[0]

    gradient = rank.gradient(denoised, disk(2))

    segmented_image = watershed(gradient, markers)
    
    return segmented_image

grabcut¶

In [37]:
def grabcut_segmentation(image):
    mask = np.zeros(image.shape[:2],np.uint8)
    bgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
    fgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
    
    rect = (50, 50, image.shape[1], image.shape[0])
    
    mask2 = cv2.grabCut(image, mask, rect, bgdModel, fgdModel, 5 , cv2.GC_INIT_WITH_RECT)
    mask2 = np.where((mask==2)|(mask==0),0,1).astype('uint8')
    img_segmented = image*mask2[:,:,np.newaxis]
    
    return img_segmented

def convert_to_2d(image):
    image_2d = image.reshape((-1,3)) 
    image_2d = np.float32(image_2d)
    
    return image_2d

In [51]:
def meanshift_segmentation(image2d, bandwidth, original_image_shape):

    clustering = MeanShift(bandwidth=bandwidth).fit(image2d)
    
    cluster_centers = clustering.cluster_centers_
    
    cluster_centers = np.uint8(cluster_centers)
    
    segmented_data = cluster_centers[clustering.labels_.flatten()] 
    segmented_image = segmented_data.reshape((original_image_shape))
    
    return segmented_image

Calculate metrics¶

In [66]:
def get_segmentation_metrics(original_image, segmented_image):
    error, precision, recall = adapted_rand_error(original_image, segmented_image)
    splits, merges = variation_of_information(original_image, segmented_image)
    
    return error, precision, recall, splits, merges
